d:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"1,100 ships disrupted by GPS attacks in Middle East"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"US-Israel strikes on Iran preceded navigation chaos"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Maritime industry scrambles for non-GPS backup solutions"}]]}]]}]}]
e:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["The Middle East’s shipping lanes—already a geopolitical pressure cooker—just became a proving ground for what happens when GPS fails at scale. Over 1,100 vessels have experienced navigation disruptions since late February, according to ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.wired.com/story/gps-attacks-middle-east-ships/","children":"new analysis"}]," from maritime security firms, a spike that aligns suspiciously with the ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/us-israel-launch-coordinated-strikes-iran-february-2024-2024-03-01/","children":"US and Israeli airstrikes on Iran"}]," on February 28. This isn’t theoretical vulnerability: container ships drifting off-course, tankers idling in limbo, and near-collisions in the Strait of Hormuz are the new normal when signals vanish or spoof."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The attacks aren’t subtle. Ships report GPS receivers feeding false coordinates—placing vessels miles from their actual position—or simply going dark. While ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.maritime-executive.com/article/gps-jamming-in-the-middle-east-reaches-critical-levels","children":"jamming has plagued the region for years"}],", the current wave is different in scale and precision. ‘It’s not just noise anymore,’ notes a cybersecurity analyst at ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://windward.ai/","children":"Windward"}],", a maritime AI firm tracking the incidents. ‘This is targeted interference designed to exploit a single point of failure.’ For an industry that runs on just-in-time logistics and razor-thin margins, the cost isn’t just operational. It’s existential."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["What’s striking isn’t the ",["$","em",null,{"children":"possibility"}]," of GPS attacks—it’s the industry’s lack of preparedness. Despite decades of warnings, ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.imo.org/en/MediaCentre/HotTopics/Pages/Navigation-safety.aspx","children":"90% of commercial ships"}]," still rely on unencrypted GPS as their primary navigation aid. The backups? Often paper charts and manual plotting, a workflow from the 1980s now colliding with 21st-century warfare."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,"$undefined",["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"The real-world cost when satellite navigation becomes a battlefield"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The ripple effects extend beyond delayed cargo. Insurance premiums for Middle East routes are climbing, with underwriters now treating GPS outages as a ‘known cyber risk.’ ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.lloyds.com/","children":"Lloyd’s of London"}]," has flagged the incidents as a potential trigger for war-risk clauses, adding another layer of friction to global supply chains. Meanwhile, ports from Dubai to Oman report congestion as vessels arrive out of sequence or require manual clearance—a logistical nightmare in a region where 30% of the world’s seaborne oil transits daily."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The silver lining? A scramble for alternatives is finally underway. Startups like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.orolia.com/","children":"Orolia"}]," are pitching quantum-resistant timing systems, while older tech—like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.gps.gov/policy/backup/eloran/","children":"eLoran"}],", a terrestrial radio navigation backup—is getting a second look. The catch? Retrofitting a fleet takes years, and the clock is ticking. ‘The market moves when the pain is acute,’ says a maritime tech investor. ‘Right now, the pain is a 10 out of 10.’"]}],"\n","$L16","\n","$L17","\n","$L18"]}]
f:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-tag w-4 h-4 text-text-secondary","aria-hidden":"true","children":[["$","path","vktsd0",{"d":"M12.586 2.586A2 2 0 0 0 11.172 2H4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v7.172a2 2 0 0 0 .586 1.414l8.704 8.704a2.426 2.426 0 0 0 3.42 0l6.58-6.58a2.426 2.426 0 0 0 0-3.42z"}],["$","circle","kqv944",{"cx":"7.5","cy":"7.5","r":".5","fill":"currentColor"}],"$undefined"]}],[["$","span","GPS Spoofing",{"className":"text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-white/5 text-text-secondary border border-white/10 hover:border-accent-cyan/30 transition-colors","children":"GPS Spoofing"}],["$","span","Maritime Logistics",{"className":"text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-white/5 text-text-secondary border border-white/10 hover:border-accent-cyan/30 transition-colors","children":"Maritime Logistics"}],["$","span","Cybersecurity Threats",{"className":"text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-white/5 text-text-secondary border border-white/10 hover:border-accent-cyan/30 transition-colors","children":"Cybersecurity Threats"}],["$","span","Global Navigation",{"className":"text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-white/5 text-text-secondary border border-white/10 hover:border-accent-cyan/30 transition-colors","children":"Global Navigation"}]]]}]}]
