16:["$","p",null,{"children":["Yet the bigger question isn’t about hardware—it’s about trust. If GPS can be weaponized this effectively, what’s next? The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.uscg.mil/","children":"US Coast Guard"}]," has warned of similar risks to port operations, while aviation regulators are quietly stress-testing backup systems. For now, the Middle East is the canary in the coal mine. But the coal mine is everywhere."]}]
17:["$","p",null,{"children":"In other words, this isn’t just a regional crisis. It’s a stress test for a world that assumed satellite navigation was a solved problem."}]
18:["$","p",null,{"children":"For ship operators, the immediate playbook is ugly but clear: budget for redundant systems, audit cyber insurance, and prepare for manual overrides. The long-term fix? A painful, expensive pivot to hybrid navigation—where no single point of failure can ground a fleet. The bill for that inertia is now due."}]
